  "extra": {
    "ds": {
      "scale": 0.7,
      "offset": [400, -50]
    },
    "description": "FrameWeaver Stacked Scene → PromptRelay → LTX 2.3 I2V Pipeline\n\nThis workflow implements the full stacked-scene video generation pipeline:\n  1. Define 5+ scenes with prompts in a single text block (FW_SceneSplitter)\n  2. Automatically iterate through scenes with auto-queue (FW_SceneIterator)\n  3. Encode each scene's temporal conditioning via PromptRelay (FW_RelayBridgeEncoder)\n  4. Generate video with LTX 2.3 I2V, using last-frame bridging for continuity\n\nUsage:\n  1. Load a starter frame (LoadImage)\n  2. Write scene prompts in FW_SceneSplitter using block syntax:\n       Scene 1:\n       A figure walks through a forest\n       Scene 2:\n       They arrive at a cabin\n     Or smart syntax: walking [0-50] | arriving [50-100]\n  3. Set frames_per_scene (97 = ~4s at 24fps)\n  4. Enable auto_queue on FW_SceneIterator\n  5. Click Queue — all 5 scenes render automatically\n  6. Each scene uses the previous scene's last frame as the start image\n\nNode chain:\n  FW_SceneIterator.scene_index → FW_SceneSplitter.scene_index\n  FW_SceneSplitter.{global,local,segments} → FW_RelayBridgeEncoder\n  FW_RelayBridgeEncoder.model → SageAttention → SamplerCustom\n  FW_RelayBridgeEncoder.positive → LTXVConditioning → SamplerCustom\n  VAEDecode.IMAGE → FW_SceneIterator.scene_video (saves + extracts last frame)\n  FW_SceneIterator.start_image → LTXVImgToVideoInplace (first-frame conditioning)"
  },
  "version": 0.4
}
